M|business-health-diagnostic|Diagnose overall SaaS business health by analyzing growth, retention, unit economics, and capital efficiency metrics together. Use this to identify problems early, prioritize actions by urgency, and d
M|business-health-diagnostic|This is not a single-metric check—it's a holistic diagnostic that connects revenue, retention, economics, and efficiency to reveal systemic issues and opportunities.
M|business-health-diagnostic|A SaaS business is healthy when four dimensions work together:
M|business-health-diagnostic|1. **Growth & Retention** — Are you growing and keeping customers?
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Revenue growth rate
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR (Net Revenue Retention)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Churn rate
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Quick Ratio
M|business-health-diagnostic|2. **Unit Economics** — Is the business model profitable at the customer level?
M|business-health-diagnostic|- CAC (Customer Acquisition Cost)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV (Lifetime Value)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV:CAC ratio
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Payback period
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Gross margin
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. **Capital Efficiency** — Are you using cash efficiently?
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Burn rate
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Runway
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Rule of 40
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Magic Number
M|business-health-diagnostic|4. **Strategic Position** — Are you positioned for sustainable success?
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Market positioning (below, at, above market pricing)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Competitive moat (network effects, data, brand)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Revenue concentration risk
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Operating leverage
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Early Stage (Pre-$10M ARR):**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Focus: Product-market fit, unit economics
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Growth: >50% YoY
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV:CAC: >3:1
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Gross Margin: >70%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Runway: >12 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Acceptable: Negative margins, high burn (if unit economics work)
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Growth Stage ($10M-$50M ARR):**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Focus: Scaling efficiently
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Growth: >40% YoY
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR: >100%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Rule of 40: >40
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Magic Number: >0.75
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Acceptable: Moderate burn if growth is strong
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Scale Stage ($50M+ ARR):**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Focus: Profitability, efficiency
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Growth: >25% YoY
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR: >110%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Rule of 40: >40
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Profit Margin: >10%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Required: Positive or near-positive cash flow
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Critical (Fix immediately):**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Runway <6 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV:CAC <1.5:1
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Churn accelerating cohort-over-cohort
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR <90%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Magic Number <0.3
M|business-health-diagnostic|**High Priority (Fix within quarter):**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Rule of 40 <25
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Payback >24 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Quick Ratio <2
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Gross margin <60%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Revenue concentration >50% in top 10 customers
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Medium Priority (Address within 6 months):**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR 90-100% (flat, not growing)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Magic Number 0.3-0.5
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Operating leverage negative
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Churn rate stable but high (>5% monthly)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- **Not a single metric:** "Revenue is growing 50%, we're great!" (ignoring burn, churn, unit economics)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- **Not stage-agnostic:** Early-stage burn is acceptable; scale-stage burn is a problem
M|business-health-diagnostic|- **Not static:** Health is directional—are metrics improving or degrading?
M|business-health-diagnostic|- **Not just numbers:** ctx matters (competitive pressure, market changes, team capacity)
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Use this when:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Preparing for board meetings or investor updates
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Quarterly business reviews (QBR)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Fundraising preparation (know your numbers)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Annual planning (identify improvement areas)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- You suspect problems but can't pinpoint them
M|business-health-diagnostic|- New PM/exec joining and needs health assessment
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Don't use this when:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- You're pre-revenue (focus on product-market fit first)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- You're in pure research mode (not enough data)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- You need tactical guidance (use specific skills: feature, channel, pricing)
M|business-health-diagnostic|Use [`workshop-facilitation`](../workshop-facilitation/SKILL.md) as the default interaction protocol for this skill.
M|business-health-diagnostic|It defines:
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ses heads-up + entry mode (Guided, ctx dump, Best guess)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- one-question turns with plain-language prompts
M|business-health-diagnostic|- progress labels (for example, ctx Qx/8 and Scoring Qx/5)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- interruption handling and pause/resume behavior
M|business-health-diagnostic|- numbered recommendations at dec points
M|business-health-diagnostic|- quick-select numbered rsp options for regular questions (include `Other (specify)` when useful)
M|business-health-diagnostic|This file defines the domain-specific assessment cnt. If there is a conflict, follow this file's domain logic.
M|business-health-diagnostic|This interactive skill asks **up to 4 adaptive questions**, then delivers a comprehensive diagnostic with prioritized recommendations.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**agt asks:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|"Let's diagnose your business health. I'll need metrics across four dimensions: growth, retention, unit economics, and capital efficiency.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Company ctx:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Stage: (Pre-$10M ARR, $10M-$50M ARR, $50M+ ARR)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Business model: (PLG, sales-led, hybrid)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Target market: (SMB, mid-market, enterprise, mixed)
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Why this matters:** Benchmarks vary by stage. Early-stage optimizes for growth; scale-stage optimizes for efficiency.
M|business-health-diagnostic|Please provide the following metrics. Use 'unknown' if you don't have a metric."
M|business-health-diagnostic|**agt asks:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|"**Growth & Retention:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|1. **Revenue:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Current MRR or ARR: $___
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Revenue growth rate: ___% (MoM or YoY)
M|business-health-diagnostic|2. **Retention:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Monthly churn rate: ___%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR (Net Revenue Retention): ___%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Quick Ratio: ___ (or I can calculate it)
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. **Expansion:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Expansion revenue as % of total MRR: ___%
M|business-health-diagnostic|4. **Cohort trends:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Are recent cohorts retaining better or worse than older cohorts?
M|business-health-diagnostic|1. Better (improving)
M|business-health-diagnostic|2. Same (stable)
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. Worse (degrading)
M|business-health-diagnostic|4. Unknown"
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Based on answers, agt evaluates:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ✅ **Healthy growth:** Growth >40% YoY (growth stage) or >25% (scale stage)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ✅ **Healthy retention:** NRR >100%, churn <5% monthly, Quick Ratio >2
M|business-health-diagnostic|- 🚨 **Growth problems:** Growth <20% YoY
M|business-health-diagnostic|- 🚨 **Retention problems:** NRR <100%, churn >5%, cohort degradation
M|business-health-diagnostic|**agt asks:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|"**Unit Economics:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|1. **Acquisition:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- CAC (Customer Acquisition Cost): $___
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Blended or by channel? (If by channel, what's your best channel CAC?)
M|business-health-diagnostic|2. **Value:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV (Lifetime Value): $___
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV:CAC ratio: ___ (or I can calculate it)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Payback period: ___ months (or I can calculate it)
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. **Margins:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Gross margin: ___%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Contribution margin (if known): ___%
M|business-health-diagnostic|4. **Trends:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Is CAC increasing, stable, or decreasing over time?
M|business-health-diagnostic|1. Decreasing (improving efficiency)
M|business-health-diagnostic|2. Stable
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. Increasing (diminishing returns)
M|business-health-diagnostic|4. Unknown"
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Based on answers, agt evaluates:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ✅ **Healthy economics:** LTV:CAC >3:1, payback <12 months, gross margin >70%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ⚠️ **Marginal economics:** LTV:CAC 2-3:1, payback 12-18 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|- 🚨 **Poor economics:** LTV:CAC <2:1, payback >24 months, gross margin <60%
M|business-health-diagnostic|**agt asks:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|"**Capital Efficiency:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|1. **Cash:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Cash balance: $___
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Monthly net burn rate: $___
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Runway: ___ months (or I can calculate it)
M|business-health-diagnostic|2. **Efficiency ratios:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Rule of 40: ___ (Growth % + Profit Margin %) (or I can calculate it)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Magic Number: ___ (S&M efficiency) (or I can calculate it)
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. **Operating expenses:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- S&M as % of revenue: ___%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- R&D as % of revenue: ___%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Is OpEx growing faster than revenue?
M|business-health-diagnostic|1. No (positive operating leverage)
M|business-health-diagnostic|2. Yes (negative operating leverage)
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. Unknown
M|business-health-diagnostic|4. **Profitability:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Profit margin: ___%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Path to profitability: (already profitable, 6-12 months, 12-24 months, >24 months, unknown)"
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Based on answers, agt evaluates:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ✅ **Healthy efficiency:** Rule of 40 >40, magic number >0.75, runway >12 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ⚠️ **Acceptable efficiency:** Rule of 40 25-40, magic number 0.5-0.75, runway 6-12 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|- 🚨 **Poor efficiency:** Rule of 40 <25, magic number <0.5, runway <6 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|**agt synthesizes all metrics and delivers:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|1. **Overall Health Score** — Healthy / Moderate / Concerning / Critical
M|business-health-diagnostic|2. **Dimension Scores** — Growth, Retention, Economics, Efficiency
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. **Red Flags** — Critical, High Priority, Medium Priority
M|business-health-diagnostic|4. **Prioritized Recommendations** — Top 3-5 actions with expected impact
M|business-health-diagnostic|5. **Stage-Appropriate Benchmarks** — How you compare to peers
M|business-health-diagnostic|**When:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Growth, retention, economics, and efficiency all meet stage-appropriate benchmarks
M|business-health-diagnostic|- No critical red flags
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Improving trends
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Output:**
