M|business-health-diagnostic|2. Fix onboarding (reduce early churn)
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. Proactive outreach to at-risk accounts
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Target: Reduce churn by 20% within 30 days
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Month 2-3: Stabilize**
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Milestone 1: Positive Unit Economics**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV:CAC >2:1 ✅
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Payback <18 months ✅
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Gross margin >60% ✅
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Milestone 2: Slowing Churn**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Churn decreasing month-over-month
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Cohort degradation stopped
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR improving toward 100%
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Milestone 3: Runway Extended**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- 12+ months runway (via fundraise or burn reduction)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Clear path to next milestone
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Metrics:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Runway: ___ months → 12+ months ✅
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV:CAC: ___:1 → >2:1 ✅
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Churn: ___% → reduced by 30% ✅
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR: ___% → improving toward 100%
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Position:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Out of crisis mode
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Stable foundation to rebuild growth
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Clear plan for next 6-12 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Don't:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Try to grow your way out of this (fix unit economics first)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Ignore the data (hope is not a str)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Scale before you fix retention (accelerates failure)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Wait until runway <3 months to fundraise (too late)
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Do:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Focus ruthlessly on retention and unit economics
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Cut costs to extend runway
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Be honest with board/investors about problems
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Move fast (you don't have time to waste)"
M|business-health-diagnostic|**When:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Runway <3 months OR
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Multiple critical failures (LTV:CAC <1:1, massive churn, no path to profitability)
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Output:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|"## 🚨🚨 Overall Health: **Critical** (Existential Crisis)
M|business-health-diagnostic|Your business is in survival mode. Immediate drastic action required.
M|business-health-diagnostic|[Similar structure to Pattern 3, but more urgent tone, shorter timelines, more drastic measures]
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Immediate Actions (This Week):**
M|business-health-diagnostic|1. Emergency board meeting
M|business-health-diagnostic|2. Fundraise immediately OR cut burn 50%+
M|business-health-diagnostic|3. Stop all non-essential spend
M|business-health-diagnostic|4. Fix top 1-2 critical issues (runway, unit economics)"
M|business-health-diagnostic|See `examples/` folder. Mini examples below:
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Metrics:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ARR: $20M, Growth: 60% YoY
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR: 115%, Churn: 2.5%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV:CAC: 4:1, Payback: 10 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Rule of 40: 50, Runway: 18 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Diagnosis:** Healthy. Scale aggressively.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Metrics:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ARR: $15M, Growth: 40% YoY
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR: 95%, Churn: 5%
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV:CAC: 3.5:1, Payback: 12 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Rule of 40: 38, Runway: 12 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Diagnosis:** Moderate. Fix retention before scaling further.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Metrics:**
M|business-health-diagnostic|- ARR: $8M, Growth: 25% YoY (slowing)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- NRR: 88%, Churn: 7% (increasing)
M|business-health-diagnostic|- LTV:CAC: 1.8:1, Payback: 20 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|- Rule of 40: 15, Runway: 8 months
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Diagnosis:** Concerning. Urgent action on retention and unit economics required.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Symptom:** "Revenue growing 50%!" (ignoring burn, churn, unit economics)
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Consequence:** Unsustainable growth. Scaling broken model.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Fix:** Look at all four dimensions together.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Symptom:** "We're not profitable yet, is that bad?" (early-stage company)
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Consequence:** Misplaced worry. Early-stage should optimize for growth and unit economics, not profitability.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Fix:** Use stage-appropriate benchmarks.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Symptom:** "Churn is 5%, let's watch it"
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Consequence:** By the time lagging indicators (churn, NRR) show problems, it's late.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Fix:** Track leading indicators (usage, engagement, onboarding completion).
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Symptom:** "NRR <100% for 3 quarters, but we'll fix it eventually"
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Consequence:** Problems compound. Becomes crisis.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Fix:** Set clear timelines. If metric doesn't improve in X time, escalate.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Symptom:** "Let's improve growth, retention, CAC, and efficiency simultaneously"
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Consequence:** Resources spread thin. Nothing improves.
M|business-health-diagnostic|**Fix:** Prioritize top 1-3 issues. Fix sequentially.
